Description: Corroded copper alloy short arrow-head of triangular section, with a conical socket; a small round hole is visible on one side.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 77 § 76, pl. xxxix, 8)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.73, p.183, pl.25)
